                    <div class="modern-grid">
                        <div class="column-3 l-column-2 m-column-0"></div>
                        <div class="column-6 l-column-8 m-column-6 newsroom-internal-body">
                            <div class="type-18-light m-type-15">
                                <p>Single-family lots in Saratoga can have one ADU—either detached, attached, or a conversion—and one Junior ADU (JADU), as long as a primary residence exists or is under construction.</p>

                            </div>
                            <div class="spacer-24 m-spacer-16"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>




                    <div class="modern-grid">
                        <div class="column-3 l-column-2 m-column-0"></div>
                        <div class="column-6 l-column-8 m-column-6 newsroom-internal-body">
                            <div class="type-18-light m-type-15">
                                <p>Multi-family lots with an existing building can have:</p>

                            </div>
                            <div class="spacer-24 m-spacer-16"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>




                <div class="modern-grid">
                    <div class="column-3 l-column-2 m-column-0"></div>
                    <div class="column-6 l-column-8 m-column-6 newsroom-internal-body">
                        <ul class="type-18-light m-type-15">
                                    <li>
                                        Up to 8 detached ADUs, as long as the number doesn’t exceed the total number of existing units
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        At least one interior ADU created from non-livable space like storage rooms or boiler rooms, with more allowed—up to one for every four existing units
                                    </li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="spacer-24 m-spacer-16"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>



                    <div class="modern-grid">
                        <div class="column-3 l-column-2 m-column-0"></div>
